{"id":"1901.05839","submitter":"Devsi Bantva","authors":"Devsi Bantva","title":"Hamiltonian chromatic number of block graphs","comments":"This is the final version appeared in Journal of Graph Algorithms and\n  Applications","journal-ref":"Journal of Graph Algorithms and Applications, 21(3), 353-369, 2017","doi":"10.7155/jgaa.00420","report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO cs.DM","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $G$ be a simple connected graph of order $n$. A hamiltonian coloring $c$\nof a graph $G$ is an assignment of colors (non-negative integers) to the\nvertices of $G$ such that $D(u, v)$ + $|c(u) - c(v)|$ $\\geq$ $n - 1$ for every\ntwo distinct vertices $u$ and $v$ of $G$, where $D(u, v)$ denotes the detour\ndistance between $u$ and $v$ in $G$ which is the length of the longest path\nbetween $u$ and $v$. The value \\emph{hc(c)} of a hamiltonian coloring $c$ is\nthe maximum color assigned to a vertex of $G$. The hamiltonian chromatic\nnumber, denoted by $hc(G)$, is min\\{$hc(c)$\\} taken over all hamiltonian\ncoloring $c$ of $G$. In this paper, we give a necessary and sufficient\ncondition to achieve a lower bound for the hamiltonian chromatic number of\nblock graphs given in [Theorem 1,On Hamiltonian Colorings of Block graphs, In:\nKaykobad, M., Petrechi, R., (eds.) WALCOM: Algorithms and Computation, LNCS:\n9627, 28-39, 2016]. We present an algorithm for optimal hamiltonian coloring of\na special class of block graphs, namely $SDB(p/2)$ block graphs. We\ncharacterize level-wise regular block graphs and extended star of blocks\nachieving this lower bound.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Jan 2019 15:26:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-18"}
